# Caddy reverse proxy for self-hosting the all-in-one CourtOps POC image on your
# own VM (DigitalOcean droplet, EC2, etc.). Caddy listens on 443, auto-obtains
# and auto-renews a Let's Encrypt cert, and proxies to the app container, which
# keeps serving plain HTTP on :8000.
#
# Prereqs on the VM:
#   - a domain's A-record pointing at the VM's public IP
#   - ports 80 (ACME challenge) and 443 open
#
# Run the app with a NAMED VOLUME so the embedded DB persists across restarts.
# A fresh volume is empty, so the entrypoint seeds the demo into it on first boot:
#   docker volume create courtops_data
#   docker run -d --name courtops --restart unless-stopped \
#       -v courtops_data:/opt/courtops/pgdata \
#       -p 127.0.0.1:8000:8000 ghcr.io/vkozyrev0/tennis-app:latest
#
# Then run Caddy (host install, or the official caddy image) with this file.
# Replace courtops.example.com with your domain — that's all Caddy needs to get
# a valid cert.

courtops.example.com {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8000
}
